<subSubSection pageId="32" pageNumber="33" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="32.[151,1437,1159,1762]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,495,1159,1185]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
Material (
<specimenCount box="[271,482,1159,1185]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" type="generic">eleven specimens</specimenCount>
):
</emphasis>
Six adult specimens (MHNCUP/RE P183–187, REP 190, formerly UP-MHNFCP- 040694, 040691, 040693, 017415, 040692 and 040695 respectively; 
<figureCitation box="[954,1057,1195,1221]" captionStart="FIGURE S" captionStartId="76.[151,248,2007,2031]" captionTargetBox="[183,1404,1119,1981]" captionTargetId="figure-54@76.[183,1404,1119,1981]" captionTargetPageId="76" captionText="FIGURE S70. Specimen of Crotaphopeltis hotamboeia (MHNCUP/REP 187), from N’dalatando. Photo by Bruna Santos." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5454123" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5454123/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Fig. S70</figureCitation>
), collected from N’Dalla Tando/ N’Dalla Tango/N’Dalla [=N’dalatando] [-9.30000º, 14.91667º, 
<quantity box="[854,923,1231,1258]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.82" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" unit="m" value="782.0">782 m</quantity>
a.s.l.] 
<collectingRegion box="[995,1263,1231,1258]" country="Angola" name="Kwanza Norte" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Kwanza Norte Province</collectingRegion>
, date unknown; 
<specimenCount box="[151,257,1267,1294]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" type="adult">one adult</specimenCount>
specimen (MHNCUP/REP 188), collected from unknown locality, date unknown; 
<specimenCount box="[1214,1321,1267,1294]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" type="adult">one adult</specimenCount>
specimen (MHNCUP/REP 189, formerly UP-MHNFCP-154857), collected from unknown locality, date unknown; 
<specimenCount pageId="32" pageNumber="33" type="juvenile">three juvenile</specimenCount>
specimens (MHNCUP/REP 337–339), collected from unknown locality, date unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="32" pageNumber="33" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="32.[151,1437,1159,1762]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,338,1375,1401]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Comments:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Laurenti" baseAuthorityYear="1768" box="[345,652,1375,1401]" class="Reptilia" family="Colubridae" genus="Crotaphopeltis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hotamboeia">
<emphasis box="[345,652,1375,1401]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Crotaphopeltis hotamboeia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a widespread species, occurring in various habitats of sub-Saharan Africa, with the exception of rainforest and arid regions; it can be found throughout 
<collectingCountry box="[1171,1253,1411,1437]" name="Angola" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Angola</collectingCountry>
apart from the southwestern desert (
<bibRefCitation author="Marques, M. P. &amp; Ceriaco, L. M. P. &amp; Blackburn, D. C. &amp; Bauer, A. M." box="[385,609,1447,1474]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" pagination="1 - 501" refId="ref38562" refString="Marques, M. P., Ceriaco, L. M. P., Blackburn, D. C. &amp; Bauer, A. M. (2018) Diversity and distribution of the amphibians and terrestrial reptiles of Angola atlas of historical and bibliographic records (1840 - 2017). Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences, Series 4, 65 (Supplement 2), 1 - 501." type="journal article" year="2018">
Marques 
<emphasis box="[490,538,1447,1473]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">et al</emphasis>
. 2018
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Engelbrecht, H. M. &amp; Branch, W. R. &amp; Greenbaum, E. &amp; Burger, M. &amp; Conradie, W. &amp; Tolley, K. A." box="[620,882,1447,1473]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" pagination="1 - 14" refId="ref36951" refString="Engelbrecht, H. M., Branch, W. R., Greenbaum, E., Burger, M., Conradie, W. &amp; Tolley, K. A. (2020) African Herald snakes, Crotaphopeltis, show population structure for a widespread generalist but deep genetic divergence for forest specialists. Journal of Zoological Systematics and Evolutionary Research, 58 (4), 1 - 14. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / jzs. 12361" type="journal article" year="2020">
Engelbrecht 
<emphasis box="[761,816,1447,1473]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">et al.</emphasis>
2020
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Ferreira, J. B." box="[899,1068,1447,1473]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" pagination="111 - 117" refId="ref37152" refString="Ferreira, J. B. (1904) Reptis e amphibios de Angola da regiao ao norte do Quanza (Colleccao Newton 1903). Jornal de Sciencias Mathematicas Physicas e Naturaes, Segunda Serie, 7 (25), 111 - 117." type="journal article" year="1904">Ferreira (1904)</bibRefCitation>
cited as “ 
<taxonomicName box="[1175,1424,1447,1473]" class="Reptilia" family="Dipsadidae" genus="Leptodira" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hotamboeia">
<emphasis box="[1175,1424,1447,1473]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Leptodira hotamboeia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” adults from “the Quanza riverbanks and the Lagoon” and “Chingo”. From the second paper, 
<bibRefCitation author="Ferreira, J. B." box="[1186,1356,1483,1510]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" pagination="159 - 171" refId="ref37198" refString="Ferreira, J. B. (1906) Algumas especies novas ou pouco conhecidas de amphibios e reptis de Angola (Coleccao Newton - 1903 - 1904). Jornal de Sciencias Mathematicas Physicas e Naturaes, Segunda Serie, 7 (26), 159 - 171." type="journal article" year="1906">Ferreira (1906)</bibRefCitation>
cited a large number of specimens (adults and juveniles), from “Cafuxi”, “Golungo Alto”, “Rio Luinha”, “Mésso Cassuco”, “Cambondo”, “N’Golla Bumba” and “Katála”. Although specimens MHNCUP/REP 183–187, REP 190 are all identified as originating from N’dalatando, it is possible that it was a transcription error and among those are some of Ferreira’s citations. The same way, specimens MHNCUP/REP 188–189, 337–339 might also comprise part of the author’s cited specimens. Through molecular analysis, 
<bibRefCitation author="Engelbrecht, H. M. &amp; Branch, W. R. &amp; Greenbaum, E. &amp; Burger, M. &amp; Conradie, W. &amp; Tolley, K. A." box="[765,1043,1663,1689]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" pagination="1 - 14" refId="ref36951" refString="Engelbrecht, H. M., Branch, W. R., Greenbaum, E., Burger, M., Conradie, W. &amp; Tolley, K. A. (2020) African Herald snakes, Crotaphopeltis, show population structure for a widespread generalist but deep genetic divergence for forest specialists. Journal of Zoological Systematics and Evolutionary Research, 58 (4), 1 - 14. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / jzs. 12361" type="journal article" year="2020">
Engelbrecht 
<emphasis box="[906,962,1663,1689]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">et al.</emphasis>
(2020)
</bibRefCitation>
recently confirmed the monophyly of 
<taxonomicName box="[184,351,1699,1726]" class="Reptilia" family="Dipsadidae" genus="Leptodira" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hotamboeia">
<emphasis box="[184,351,1699,1726]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">C. hotamboeia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The authors also identified six different infraspecific clades from the analysis, with “clade 2” being restricted to the southern tip of the 
<collectingCountry box="[613,827,1735,1761]" name="Republic of the Congo" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Republic of Congo</collectingCountry>
extending to 
<collectingCountry box="[978,1064,1735,1761]" name="Angola" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Angola</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
